The paper focuses on a hybrid approach for vulnerability discovery in software applications using fuzz testing and symbolic execution. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with software testing and analysis. The paper also mentions uncovering subtle errors and vulnerabilities, which suggests a focus on security (cs.CR). The implementation is based on Java programs, indicating a focus on programming languages (cs.PL). The use of symbolic execution suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY), while the use of fuzz testing suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) again.
